However , it is not a reasonable idea to use RFID to track people in human implants or RFID tags on daily products like watches or clothes , it did provide convenience in a certain situation .
The biggest difference between humans and animals or any other object is that we have self-esteem or we need a basic respect to our peers .
One of the basic rights of human is a right to privacy .
In any period of time , as long as we do not offensive others , we should enjoy the right to privacy .
However , the idea of using RFID to track people violating our need for privacy .
Since RFID tags attached to the product could remain functional for a long period of time , it could be misused for surveillance purposes which are not related to the industry production or supply activities .
For example , a consumer buys a product of RFID in the supermarket .
As the RFID is embedded within the product , people who have access to the information definitely can track him .
However , the consumer may not be aware of the function of the tag , so this action could reveal the sensitive information of the consumers like home address , work address to someone who is not authorized to get the information .
If this piece of information was misused , chances are high that the consumer would suffer losses like financial loss or even cause danger to the life of the consumer .
Moreover , if the product is what one needs to use every day like clothes or shoes , then the location of one will be revealed every second .
This is just like there is an invisible stalker behind you .
It is not only scary but also illegal .
Although someone would say the information is secure very well and will not be released or misused for any purpose , it is still not appropriate .
We can think about this scenario : the location of us going about daily life will be sent to a computer to be processed and stored every second .
Does this sounds reasonable to you ?
As what we have mentioned above , as human beings , we should enjoy our privacy during our life as long as we do not cause harm to others .
However , RFID will violate our right to privacy during our shopping activity .
Therefore , RFID should not be used to track people no matter through human implants or tags on products .
