In a modern society , public surveillance is becoming a normal phenomenon .
In the United States , after the horrible attack on 11 September , the US congress passed the Patriot Act , which is mainly to increase domestic surveillance , to counter against the terrorists .
However , although these bureaucratic actions prevented another similar attack from happening again , the act was widely criticized for its violations over individual privacy .
With the development of surveillance technologies such as RFID , spy on the population can be much easier , which will create even worse scenery for the citizens .
In this paper , the incorrectness of using technologies such as RFID to track people will be proved in the discussion of violation of privacy , the trend of misuse such measures and the enhancement of the totalitarian rule of the authority .
First , a violation of privacy would be dramatically increased .
Typically , the RFID tags are small devices with a read-only chip .
The regular distance for data exchange could be several meters .
Once such chips are loaded with personal information and implanted in individuals , all the information about his or her life can be recorded .
Some supporters might argue that it will more convenient to use RFID for identification at places like airports and check points .
However , the fact is that such technology will create check points everywhere .
Furthermore , such tracking of individual was done without permission from the subject peoples .
That is to say , people will be surveilled by every moment without awareness .
In such situations , individuals will lose their basic privacy .
Second , when technology like RFID is widely used , there will be a trend of misuse such technology .
An important feature of RFID is a minimal security .
Since it is read-only , the card could not protect itself .
Moreover , almost every one can gain access to the card reader as a reader requires only simple technology .
Then , if a business man wants to defeat his competitor , he can just buy a reader and spying for commercial secrets .
Hence , once RFID is widely used , people are very likely to spy on each other , which would destroy trust , respect and many moral values .
Third , to use the surveillance technologies will enhance the totalitarian power at the authority .
The government is supposed to serve the people .
However , once the government gathered too much power , a democracy may be turned into totalitarianism , and such surveillance technology provides the measures .
Spy and collect excessive information about individuals is the first step .
When government be able to find out all the precise information to its citizens , it can gradually applied control over them .
Consequently , the government is very likely to turn to is the totalitarian authority , which would be the worst scenery and tragedy for every single citizen .
All in all , surveillance technologies such as RFID should not be used to track general population for a violation of privacy , the trend of misuse such measures and the enhancement of the totalitarian power of the authority .
Privacy must be respected , and power over others should be controlled .
Without such surveillance technology , we can still live a better future .
With the development of the science and technology , people nowadays are living under various surveillance , for example , CCTV can be seen almost everywhere in public areas .
